This is the complete works of MTH1021
MTH1021 Mathematical Methods I is a core first-year mathematics module that runs for the full year. 
The module begins with a revision of basic calculus and elementary functions. 
These fundamental topics form the basis for investigating the properties of functions using derivatives, integrals and power series. Differential equations, complex numbers, vector analysis, matrix manipulation and calculus in several variables are covered in the module.
It thus provides many useful mathematical tools for applications in mechanics, statistics, quantum theory etc
